    "name": "Horn of Clairvoyance",
    "type": "equipment",
    "img": "icons/commodities/treasure/horn-spiral-pink.webp",
    "system": {
        "description": {
            "value": "<p><span style=\"font-family:Signika, sans-serif\"><em style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text\">This lacquered horn has been enchanted to allow a diviner to grant divination magic to those without the ability to cast the spell themselves. While anyone can use it, it must be recharged by a diviner, and the magic is somewhat limited.</em></span></p><p>When a spellcaster casts the <em>@UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-spells.Item.ww8DtX0ROIGyTnYj]{Clairvoyance}</em> spell, they can use this horn as the material component. When they do, they do not cast the spell normally. Instead, the spell is stored in the horn. Any creature can then cast <em>Clairvoyance</em> with the horn as an action by holding it to their ear, but they can only hear, not see, from the location chosen for the spell.</p><p>Once the horn has been used, it must be recharged by casting <em>Clairvoyance</em> on the eye again.</p>",
